ExamFlow Admin Panel Specification

1. Admin Panel Goals
The admin panel should allow the internal team to manage content, users, questions, tests, moderation, analytics, and operational settings.

It should be secure, fast, and easy for non-technical staff to use.

2. Primary Admin Roles
- Super admin.
- Admin.
- Content manager.
- Reviewer.
- Moderator.
- Support staff.

3. Admin Principles
- Role-based access control.
- Clear dashboard views.
- Fast content workflows.
- Easy search and filtering.
- Strong audit logging.
- Minimal clicks for routine tasks.
- Secure approval and publishing flow.

4. Core Admin Modules
- Dashboard.
- User management.
- Exam management.
- Subject and syllabus management.
- Chapter and topic management.
- Content management.
- Question bank management.
- Test management.
- Community moderation.
- Analytics and reports.
- Notification management.
- AI configuration.
- Settings and permissions.

5. Dashboard Requirements
The dashboard should show:
- Total users.
- Active users.
- New registrations.
- Questions published.
- Content items published.
- Pending moderation items.
- Tests attempted.
- Average score.
- Retention metrics.
- Revenue metrics if monetization is enabled later.

6. User Management
Admin should be able to:
- View all users.
- Search users.
- Filter by role, status, exam, and date.
- Block or unblock users.
- Reset roles and permissions.
- View profile details.
- Review user activity history.

7. Exam Management
Admin should be able to:
- Create exams.
- Edit exam details.
- Enable or disable exams.
- Control syllabus depth.
- Manage exam-specific language support.

8. Syllabus Management
Admin should be able to:
- Create subjects.
- Create chapters.
- Create topics.
- Reorder syllabus items.
- Mark items as draft, active, or archived.
- Link content and questions to topics.

9. Content Management
Admin should be able to:
- Create and edit notes.
- Add textbook-style explanations.
- Upload diagrams and images.
- Manage summaries and revision sheets.
- Preview content before publishing.
- Schedule publishing.
- Track version history.

10. Question Bank Management
Admin should be able to:
- Create new questions.
- Edit existing questions.
- Assign difficulty levels.
- Attach explanations.
- Tag questions.
- Import bulk questions.
- Review accuracy and reports.
- Archive outdated questions.

11. Test Management
Admin should be able to:
- Create topic quizzes.
- Create subject tests.
- Create full mock tests.
- Add or remove questions from tests.
- Set duration and scoring rules.
- Publish or unpublish tests.
- Duplicate existing tests.

12. Community Moderation
Admin should be able to:
- View submission queue.
- Review user-generated questions or notes.
- Approve, reject, or edit submissions.
- Add moderation comments.
- Track reviewer actions.
- Escalate flagged content.

13. Analytics Dashboard
Admin should be able to view:
- Daily active users.
- Weekly active users.
- Retention trends.
- Study progress trends.
- Top-performing content.
- Weak-topic analytics.
- Question accuracy rates.
- Test performance trends.
- Contributor activity.
- Conversion metrics later if needed.

14. Notification Management
Admin should be able to:
- Send announcements.
- Send push notifications.
- Send email campaigns.
- Segment users by exam or activity.
- View delivery and read status.

15. AI Configuration
If AI features are enabled, admin should be able to:
- Toggle AI modules on or off.
- Configure prompt templates.
- Set safety rules.
- Review AI usage logs.
- View AI cost or quota metrics.
- Restrict AI features by role or exam plan.

16. Search and Filtering
The admin panel must support:
- Global search.
- Table filtering.
- Date range filters.
- Exportable reports.
- Sorting by status, activity, and created date.

17. Audit Logging
Log all important actions:
- Content edits.
- Publishing actions.
- Role changes.
- Test updates.
- Approvals and rejections.
- AI configuration changes.
- Permission modifications.

18. Permissions Model
Example permissions:
- view_users.
- edit_users.
- create_content.
- edit_content.
- publish_content.
- moderate_submissions.
- manage_tests.
- view_analytics.
- manage_notifications.
- manage_ai_settings.
- manage_permissions.

19. UI Structure
Recommended admin layout:
- Left sidebar for modules.
- Top bar for search, notifications, and account.
- Main content area with data tables and forms.
- Quick actions for common tasks.
- Clear status badges and filters.

20. Admin Table Standards
Tables should support:
- Pagination.
- Bulk actions.
- Column sorting.
- Filter chips.
- Row actions.
- Export CSV or similar if needed.

21. Content Workflow
Suggested flow:
1. Creator drafts content.
2. Reviewer checks quality.
3. Admin approves or edits.
4. Content is published.
5. Content changes are logged.
6. Content is re-reviewed when updated.

22. Question Workflow
Suggested flow:
1. Question is created or imported.
2. Reviewer checks correctness.
3. Admin assigns metadata.
4. Question is linked to topic.
5. Question is published to tests or practice.

23. Moderation Workflow
Suggested flow:
1. User submits content.
2. Item enters moderation queue.
3. Reviewer checks clarity and correctness.
4. Item is approved, edited, or rejected.
5. Final action is logged.

24. Reporting Needs
The admin panel should support:
- Content reports.
- User reports.
- Test reports.
- Moderation reports.
- Activity reports.
- Exportable snapshots for business review.

25. Security Requirements
- Admin login protection.
- Session timeout.
- Two-factor authentication if possible.
- Strict role permissions.
- CSRF protection.
- Audit logs for sensitive actions.
- IP or device restrictions if needed later.

26. Performance Requirements
- Fast table loading.
- Efficient server-side pagination.
- Cached dashboard totals.
- Async export jobs.
- Lightweight forms and modals.

27. Future Admin Features
- Revenue management.
- Subscription plans.
- Coupon controls.
- Referral tracking.
- Coaching partnership tools.
- Teacher/instructor management.
- Multi-language content administration.

28. Admin Summary
The admin panel should give the team full operational control over content, questions, tests, users, and moderation while remaining simple enough for daily use.

End of file.
